<paragraph blockId="85.[151,1323,1800,1896]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,614,1835,1861]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Distribution: WEST PALAEARCTIC:</emphasis>
Scattered record in Levant and 
<collectingCountry box="[971,1016,1836,1862]" name="Iran" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rasmont, P. &amp; Dehon, M." box="[1031,1311,1835,1862]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" refId="ref106184" refString="Rasmont, P. &amp; Dehon, M. (2014) Atlas of the European Bees: genus Ancyla. 1 st Edition. STEP Project, Atlas Hymenoptera, Mons, Gembloux. Available from: http: // www. atlashymenoptera. net / page. aspx? ID = 262 (accessed 10 November 2020)" type="url" year="2014">Rasmont &amp; Dehon 2014</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,1870,1896]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Literature.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke, K." box="[289,474,1870,1896]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" pagination="183 - 195" refId="ref108086" refString="Warncke, K. (1979) Beitrag zur Bienenfauna des Iran. 10. Die Gattung Ancyla Lep., mit einer Revision der Bienengattung Ancyla Lep. Bollettino del Museo civico di storia naturale di Venezia, 30, 183 - 195." type="journal article" year="1979">Warncke (1979)</bibRefCitation>
: Reported from Beirut, 1912.
</paragraph>
