</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="85.[151,497,2010,2037]" box="[151,497,2010,2037]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,497,2010,2037]" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Scopoli, 1770" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1770" box="[234,497,2010,2037]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="85" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,332,2010,2037]" italics="true" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Nomada</emphasis>
Scopoli, 1770
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1437,151,393]" box="[151,275,151,177]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">16 species.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
This understudied and taxonomically challenging genus in the southern part of the West Palaearctic is probably one of the most species rich genera present in 
<collectingCountry box="[665,763,223,249]" name="Lebanon" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
because of the high species richness of their principal hosts, the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[193,288,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[193,288,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Andrena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Future thorough revision of Lebanese 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1770" box="[733,828,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[733,828,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Nomada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
material is likely to substantially increase the number of species present. Based on the ratio of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1770" box="[623,718,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Nomada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[623,718,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Nomada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[758,853,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[758,853,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Andrena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[894,989,295,321]" name="Portugal" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Portugal</collectingCountry>
(3:5; 
<bibRefCitation author="Baldock, D. &amp; Wood, T. &amp; Cross, I. &amp; Smit, J." box="[1060,1290,295,321]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 164" refId="ref100007" refString="Baldock, D., Wood, T., Cross, I. &amp; Smit, J. (2018) The Bees of Portugal (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). Entomofauna Supplement, S 22, 1 - 164." type="journal article" year="2018">
Baldock 
<emphasis box="[1163,1222,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, T. J. &amp; Cross, I. &amp; Baldock, D." pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="201 - 228" refId="ref108378" refString="Wood, T. J., Cross, I. &amp; Baldock, D. (2020 b) Updates to the bee fauna of Portugal with the description of three new Iberian Andrena species (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). Zootaxa, 4790 (2), 201 - 228. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4790.2.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Wood 
<emphasis box="[1378,1437,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">et al.</emphasis>
2020b
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[285,386,331,357]" name="Morocco" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Morocco</collectingCountry>
(2:5; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lhomme, P. &amp; Michez, D. &amp; Christmann, S. &amp; Scheuhl, E. &amp; El Abdouni, I. &amp; Hamroud, L. &amp; Ihsane, O. &amp; Sentil, A. &amp; Chrif Smaili, M. &amp; Schwarz, M. &amp; Dathe, H. H. &amp; Straka, J. &amp; Pauly, A. &amp; Schmid &amp; Egger, C. &amp; Patiny, S. &amp; Terzo, M. &amp; Muller, A. &amp; Praz, C. &amp; Risch, S. &amp; Kasparek M. &amp; Kuhlmann, M. &amp; Wood, T. J. &amp; Bogusch, P. &amp; Ascher, J. &amp; Rasmont, P." box="[454,685,331,357]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" refId="ref103319" refString="Lhomme, P., Michez, D., Christmann, S., Scheuhl, E., El Abdouni, I., Hamroud, L., Ihsane, O., Sentil, A., Chrif Smaili, M., Schwarz, M., Dathe, H. H., Straka, J., Pauly, A., Schmid - Egger, C., Patiny, S., Terzo, M., Muller, A., Praz, C., Risch, S., Kasparek M., Kuhlmann, M., Wood, T. J., Bogusch, P., Ascher, J. &amp; Rasmont, P. (2020) The wild bees (Hymenoptera: Apoidea) of Morocco, Zootaxa, 4892 (1), 159 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4892.1.1" type="book" year="2020">
Lhomme 
<emphasis box="[562,618,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
), we estimate a likely Lebanese species richness of between 34–52 species.
</paragraph>
